ts understand local notions of place and culture. Full of anecdotes and interviews with the market's primary figures, Real Pigs reminds us that what we eat and why have implications that resonate throughout the wider social, cultural, and historical world.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 0aCooking (Pork)zNorth Carolina. 0aPork industry and tradezNorth Carolina. 4aAssociation for the Study of Food and Society Book Award Winner. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh1 aMaclean, Eliza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCurtis, Jennifer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO'sullivan, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCallaghan, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlynn, Ross, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSuchoff, Sam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlacklin, Sarah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRajendran, Vimala, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCramer, Will, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311070808040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822374237zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822374237423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822374237.jpg  a978-3-11-070808-0  DUK Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles